The paper deals with the theory of interleaving distance on persistence modules, which is a topic in computational topology and topological data analysis. The paper presents results related to the algebraic and metric properties of interleaving distance on multidimensional persistence modules. This makes it likely to belong to sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
